it.emarolab.owloop.core

Interface ObjectProperty.Range<O,J,Y>

  • Type Parameters:
    O - the type of ontology in which the axioms for classes will be applied.
    J - the type of the described class.
    Y - the type of restriction for the EntitySet managed by this Descriptor.
    All Superinterfaces:
    Axiom, Axiom.Descriptor<O,J>, ObjectProperty<O,J>
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    ObjectPropertyExpression.Range
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    DomainRangeObjectPropertyDesc, FullObjectPropertyDesc
    Enclosing interface:
    ObjectProperty<O,J>

    public static interface ObjectProperty.Range<O,J,Y>
extends ObjectProperty<O,J>
    Implementation of this interface enables a ObjectProperty to have the ObjectProperty.Range expression.

    This descriptor synchronises the definition of the range of the grounded data property. Definition is defined as a conjunction of restriction properties that create a super class of the described ontological class. The restriction can be of the following types:

    • class restriction: a range is restricted to a class.
    • data restriction: a range is defined to have data properties into a given range. It is also possible to describe the cardinality of this restriction to be: existential (some), universal (all), minimal, maximal and exact.
    • object restriction: a range is defined to have data properties into a given class. It is also possible to describe the cardinality of this restriction to be: existential (some), universal (all), minimal, maximal and exact.
    If this expression is used, it is not possible to use the build() operation since the restrictions are not simple OWL entities like OWLClass, OWLIndividual, OWLObjectProperty and OWLDataProperty.

        This method is used to update specific Axiom.EntitySet (or Axiom.ExpressionEntitySet) by synchronizing the internal state of the descriptor with the queried OWL structure, such that they are equal. It is based on EntitySet#synchroniseFrom(EntitySet).
